fields.name: NSCPPharmacySurveyIntroWording
fields.fieldText:
The NSCP is working to ensure staffing levels in community pharmacy enable safe and appropriate care.


Pharmacy managers provide critical data on the type of pharmacy they manage and its current staffing complement. Your answers to the following questions will be used by the NSCP to annually update the StaffWISE staffing score for your pharmacy.

fields.name: NSCPPharmacySurveyIntroWording1
fields.fieldText: Please ensure your answers are as accurate as possible.

fields.name: PharmacyCharacteristicsSubHeader
fields.fieldText: Pharmacy Name and Licence # will be collected in the renewal process for linkage

fields.name: Section1Header
fields.fieldText: 1. Which of the following best describes your pharmacy?

fields.name: Section2Header
fields.fieldText: 2a. Does your pharmacy hold off-site vaccination clinics?

fields.name: X2bSectionHeader
fields.fieldText: 2b. If yes, please indicate the dates of any off-site vaccine clinics held within the last 12 months and the approximate total number of vaccinations delivered through these clinics.

fields.name: Section3Header
fields.fieldText: 3. Is your pharmacy co-located with a medical clinic?

fields.name: Section4Header
fields.fieldText: 4. Is your pharmacy co-located with a Community Pharmacy Primary Care (CPPC) Clinic?

fields.name: A5_Message
fields.fieldText: 5a. What are the typical hours of operation for the dispensary?

fields.name: StartTimeMessage
fields.fieldText: Please select start and end times from the 24-hour dropdowns below

fields.name: TypicalHours
fields.fieldText:
5b. What are the typical hours of operation for the CPPC clinic?

Indicate Start and End Time for each day of the week using a 24-hour clock (e.g., 09:00-17:00)

fields.name: Section_6A_New
fields.fieldText: 6a. How many total pharmacy staff members do you currently have in the following roles in the dispensary (e.g., total headcount of employees). Please enter "0" for any roles that you do not currently have on your roster.

fields.name: PharmacyAssistantIncludesCashiers_6a
fields.fieldText: Pharmacy Assistant (includes cashiers working in the dispensary)

fields.name: Section_6b_New
fields.fieldText: 6b. How many total pharmacy staff members do you currently have in the following roles in the CPPC Clinic (e.g., total headcount of employees). Please enter "0" for any roles that you do not currently have on your roster.

fields.name: PharmacyAssistantDispensaryCashiers_6b
fields.fieldText: Pharmacy Assistant (includes cashiers working in the dispensary)

fields.name: Section_7a_New
fields.fieldText: 7a. How many total labour hours do you currently schedule for each of the following roles in the dispensary in a typical week? A typical week represents the most common weekly schedule at your pharmacy. Pease enter "0" for any roles that you do not currently schedule/have budget for in a typical week.

fields.name: PharmacyAssistantCashiersDispensary_7a
fields.fieldText: Pharmacy Assistant (includes cashiers working in the dispensary)

fields.name: Section_7b_New
fields.fieldText: 7b. How many total labour hours do you currently schedule for each of the following roles in the CPPCC clinic in a typical week? A typical week represents the most common weekly schedule at your pharmacy. Please enter "0" for any roles that you do not currently schedule/have budget for in a typical week.

fields.name: PharmacyAssistantIncludesCashiers_7b
fields.fieldText: Pharmacy Assistant (includes cashiers working in the dispensary)

fields.name: Survey_8a
fields.fieldText: 8a. How many hours of pharmacist overlap does your pharmacy currently schedule in the dispensary in a typical week? A typical week represents the most common weekly schedule at your pharmacy.

fields.name: question_8b
fields.fieldText: 8b. If your pharmacy is a CPPC clinic, How many hours of pharmacist overlap does your pharmacy currently schedule in the CPPC clinic in a typical week? A typical week represents the most common weekly schedule at your pharmacy.

fields.name: Question_9a
fields.fieldText: 9a. How many hours of pharmacy technician overlap does your pharmacy currently schedule in the dispensary in a typical week?

fields.name: Question_9b
fields.fieldText: 9b. How many hours of pharmacy technician overlap does your pharmacy currently schedule in the CPPC clinic in a typical week?

fields.name: Question_10a
fields.fieldText:
10a. How many full-time equivalent (FTE) vacancies do you currently have in the dispensary for each of the following roles?

Note: An FTE is calculated as number of hours worked by an employee divided by the number of hours in a typical full-time work week (e.g., if a work week consists of 40 hours, a full-time vacancy would be 1 FTE, a 20 hour/week vacancy would be 0.5 FTE). Please enter 0 if there are no vacancies in a category.

fields.name: PharmacyAssistantIncludesCashiers_10a
fields.fieldText: Pharmacy Assistant (includes cashiers working in the dispensary)

fields.name: Question_10b
fields.fieldText:
10b. How many full-time equivalent (FTE) vacancies do you currently have in the CPPC clinic for each of the following roles?

Note: An FTE is calculated as number of hours worked by an employee divided by the number of hours in a typical full-time work week (e.g., if a work week consists of 40 hours, a full-time vacancy would be 1 FTE, a 20 hour/week vacancy would be 0.5 FTE). Please enter 0 if there are no vacancies in a category.

fields.name: PharmacyAssistantIncludesCashiers_10b
fields.fieldText: Pharmacy Assistant (includes cashiers working in the dispensary)

fields.name: Wording_11
fields.fieldText: Note: All dispenses and clinical activities for your pharmacy are captured directly by the NSCP using NS DIS and Pharmacare data.

fields.name: Question_11
fields.fieldText: 11. What is the percent breakdown of prescription types dispensed at your pharmacy? The total must add to 100%

fields.name: Section12Header
fields.fieldText: 12. What types of dispensing technology are utilized at your pharmacy?

fields.name: DisplayText_13
fields.fieldText:
13. What is the percent breakdown for each prescription type filled using dispensing technology versus NOT using dispensing technology? For each type filled, the percentage using dispensing technology and the percentage NOT using dispensing technology must add to 100%


Note: dispensing technology includes counting (e.g., Accu-Count), preparation (e.g.,Methameasure), and packaging (e.g., Blistassist, PACMED, Parata) technologies.

fields.name: DisplayText_14
fields.fieldText: 14. What is the percent breakdown for each prescription type filled onsite versus central fill? For each prescription type, the percentage entered for filled on-site and central fill must add to 100%
